International Brief -- Grand Metropolitan PLC:
   Food and Drinks Company
   Slates 2-for-1 Stock Split
He said the company's American depositary receipts (ADRs)
also will be split.
   In a down market, Grand Met closed at 947 pence ($16.53),
down one pence.
   Mr. Sheppard also said at the regular annual meeting that
the first half of the current financial year will be "in line
with last year," without counting gains from the recent sale
of Grand Met's dairy businesses. In the year ended Sept. 30,
Grand Met reported a 4.8% rise in pretax profit to #963
million ($1.68 billion) from #919 million the year before.